WHEREAS, Jonathan Lucroy enjoyed a distinguished twelve-year Major League
Baseball career from 2010 to 2021, playing for nine teams and compiling over 1,000 hits,
217 doubles, 108 home runs, and 548 runs batted in across 1,210 games; and
WHEREAS, he earned Major League Baseball All-Star selections in 2014 and 2016
and wass ranked fourth in the selection of the National League Most Valuable Player in
2014, the same season in which he set the Major League Baseball single-season doubles
record for a catcher with 53 doubles; and
WHEREAS, Jonathan Lucroy represented the United States in international
competitions, participating in the 2013 World Baseball Classic and helping Team USA
capture the gold medal in 2017; and
WHEREAS, following his retirement, he has remained committed to the
development of young athletes through coaching at the high school level and participating
in the Team USA Youth National Team Program, while prioritizing faith, family, and
community; and
WHEREAS, his career reflects excellence, leadership, sportsmanship, and
dedication, bringing pride to the state of Louisiana, and serving as an inspiration to future
generations of athletes.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
commend Jonathan Lucroy on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports
Hall of Fame.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
Jonathan Lucroy.
